    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To use lighting, add a light node to the scene. Because lights are nodes, they can be moved or perform actions just like other nodes. However, light nodes are invisible except through their effects on sprite nodes configured to interact with them. When a sprite node is affected by a light, the lighting properties of the light node and the lighting properties of the sprite node determine what is rendered. Lighting may affect how unrelated portions of the scene are rendered. For example, if a sprite is configured to cast a shadow, the shadow is rendered on top of other content."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sklightnode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object and an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skspritenode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object add lighting to the scene if all of the following  are true:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "The light node and the sprite node are both in the scene."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "The light node’s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sklightnode/1519826-enabled"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property is "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "The light node’s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sklightnode/1519940-categorybitmask"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property and one of the sprite’s lighting masks are logically combined using an AND operation, and the result is a nonzero number."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sklightnode#1965813"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " describes the different kinds of effects that can be generated by a light, based on which mask is being tested on the sprite."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "table",
          "header": "row",
          "rows": [
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Sprite Node Mask"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Effect"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skspritenode/1519637-lightingbitmask"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "The sprite is lit by the light with specular, diffuse, and ambient lighting."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skspritenode/1520325-shadowcastbitmask"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "When the light casts a ray that intersects the sprite, a shadow is projected past the sprite, rendered on top of any content that is below the sprite."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skspritenode/1519974-shadowedbitmask"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "If the sprite is inside a shadow cast by a light and the sprite has a lower z position than the light, the shadow affects how the sprite is lit."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "1965813",
            "title": "Table 1",
            "abstract": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Lighting effects"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If any of the criteria are not met, the sprite is considered unlit and is rendered using the default behavior."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
